              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a>
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+491732585212" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">+49 173 25 85 212</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Small Business Exemption</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              As a small entrepreneur in accordance with national law, we do not charge VAT, and this tax is not disclosed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t-2 border-gray-300">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-8 font-headline">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">Last updated: December 2025</p>
            
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              As the operator of this website, Björn Gaworski-Dammann (hereinafter "I" or "We"), take the protection of your personal data very seriously. This policy is designed to be transparent and compliant with the European Union's General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the German Telemedia Act (TMG)/Digital Services Act (DDG).
            </p>

            <div class="pt-6">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Responsible Body (Controller)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">The responsible body for data processing on this website is:</p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <p><strong>Björn Gaworski-Dammann</strong></p>
                <p>
                  Schimmelmannstraße 5<br>
                  22043 Hamburg<br>
                  Germany
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a>
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Telephone:</strong> <a href="tel:+491732585212" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">+49 173 25 85 212</a>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Scope and Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
                Crucially, this website is designed to be fully GDPR-compliant by default, as it collects NO personal data.
              </p>

              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.1. No Data Collection by the Website Operator</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    This website has been designed to avoid the collection of any personal data.
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li><strong>No Cookies:</strong> This website does not use any first-party or third-party cookies (e.g., tracking cookies, preference cookies, or analytical cookies).</li>
                    <li><strong>No Analytics Tools:</strong> No external analytics services (such as Google Analytics, Matomo, or similar) are embedded.</li>
                    <li><strong>No Contact Forms:</strong> You cannot submit data via a contact form on this site.</li>
                    <li><strong>No Social Media Plugins:</strong> There are no embedded social media buttons or plugins that transmit data to third-party providers (like Facebook, LinkedIn, or X).</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.2. Processing of Data through Direct Communication</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    If you choose to contact me via the provided email address (<a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a>) or telephone number (<a href="tel:+491732585212" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">+49 173 25 85 212</a>), any personal data transmitted (such as your name, email address, phone number, and the content of your message) will be processed solely for the purpose of handling your inquiry and, if applicable, initiating a contract.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. b GDPR (for contract initiation) or Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in responding to your communication).
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    <strong>Retention:</strong> Data will be retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose of the communication or to comply with legal retention periods (e.g., commercial or tax law).
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Server Log Files (Data Collected by the Hosting Provider)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                The provider of the pages (web hoster) automatically collects and stores information in so-called server log files, which your browser automatically transmits to us. These include:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li>Browser type and browser version</li>
                <li>Operating system used</li>
                <li>Referrer URL</li>
                <li>Hostname of the accessing computer</li>
                <li>Time of the server request</li>
                <li>IP address</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                This data is not merged with other data sources. The collection of this data is necessary to enable the technical operation of the website and to ensure system security.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR (Legitimate interest in the technical provision and security of the website).
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Your Rights as a Data Subject (GDPR Rights)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                Under the GDPR, you have the right to:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li><strong>Right of Access (Art. 15 GDPR):</strong> Request confirmation as to whether personal data concerning you is being processed, and access to that data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Rectification (Art. 16 GDPR):</strong> Request the correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Erasure ('Right to be Forgotten') (Art. 17 GDPR):</strong> Request the deletion of your personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Restriction of Processing (Art. 18 GDPR):</strong> Request the restriction of the processing of your personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Data Portability (Art. 20 GDPR):</strong> Receive the personal data concerning you in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Object (Art. 21 GDPR):</strong> Object to the processing of your personal data, particularly if the processing is based on legitimate interests (Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR).</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
                If you believe that the processing of your personal data violates data protection law, you have the <strong>Right to Lodge a Complaint with a competent supervisory authority</strong> (Art. 77 GDPR). The supervisory authority responsible for me is:
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                Hamburg Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information<br>
                Klosterwall 6 (Block C)<br>
                20095 Hamburg<br>
                Germany<br>
                Phone: +49 40 428 54 4040<br>
                Email: mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                We reserve the right to amend this data protection declaration at any time in compliance with legal requirements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

